    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
          Lithuanian contingency plans
</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/lithuania-evacuation-plan-vilnius-belarus-kaliningrad.png" alt="Map highlighting Lithuania and neighboring regions, Belarus, and Kaliningrad" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Lithuania’s geography makes it susceptible to a Russian invasion. The country lies between Belarus, a strong Russian ally, and Russian territory along the Baltic Sea.</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           Amid growing concerns over a Russian invasion, officials in Vilnius, Lithuania, have <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-04-2025-h1-1-announced-an-evacuation-plan?source=website" target="_blank">announced an evacuation plan</a> for the city's residents. Vilnius lies 20 miles (35 km) from the border with Belarus, a strong Russian ally, and the country shares a border with Kaliningrad, a heavily fortified Russian exclave.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">
          The evacuation plan includes 150 routes and designated points in each neighborhood. Communication will occur through SMS alerts, sirens, and a mobile app that is currently under development. Roads and bridges will be expanded to allow for smooth evacuation. Mayor Valdas Benkunskas stated that evacuation would be a last resort if the city's defenses fail.</p>
        
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
